Preheat the #oven to 240°C/220°C fan/gas mark 9.

Halve the @baby potatoes{400%g} lengthways (quarter any larger pieces). Pop them
onto a lined #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{to taste}, season with
@Central American Style Spice Mix{1%sachet}, @salt{to taste} and
@pepper{to taste} then toss to coat.

Spread out in a single layer. When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until
golden, ~{25-35%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

Pick @sage{10%g} leaves. Trim the bottom 2cm from @broccolini{150%g}.

Lay @Irish chicken breast{320%g} on a #chopping board{}. Place hand flat on top.
IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw chicken. Slice
horizontally until there are 2cm left (don't cut all the way through). Open it up
like a book.

> TIP: Notice a stronger smell from your chicken? Don't worry, this is due to
> the vacuum packing used to keep it fresh and is normal. It will still be
> delicious once cooked!

Drizzle the chicken with @oil{to taste} and season lightly with @salt{to taste}
and @pepper{to taste}. Divide the @grated Italian Style hard cheese{25%g}
between the chicken breasts, pressing down firmly so it adheres.

Carefully roll the chicken up, encasing the filling. Wrap half the
@Serrano ham{65%g} tightly around the chicken breasts.

Place a pan over medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{to taste}. Once hot,
add the broccolini and season with salt and pepper.

Fry for ~{2-3%minutes} then add a splash of @water{to taste} and cover with a #lid
or some #foil{}. Cook until the broccolini is tender, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Once cooked, remove from the pan and cover to keep warm.

Return the pan to medium-high heat with a drizzle of oil. Fry the chicken,
~{4-5%minutes} each side, until the bacon is cooked through.

Add a splash of @water{to taste}, cover and cook for ~{8-10%minutes}. IMPORTANT:
Chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Shift the chicken to one side of the pan. Add 3 tbsp @butter{to taste} to the
empty side and melt. Fry the sage in the butter until crispy, ~{2-3%minutes}.
Baste the chicken in the sage butter.

Serve the wrapped chicken with the roast baby potatoes and pan-fried broccolini
alongside. Drizzle any remaining sage butter over the chicken.